This project inlines SVG icon geometry from Lucide (https://lucide.dev), plus a
few third-party brand marks (see "Brand marks" below).

The `<path>` / `<circle>` / etc. geometry all lives in one module,
`ui/src/ui/icon.gleam`, which both the `ui` elements (accordion, checkbox,
command, dialog, sidebar, spinner) and the documentation examples import. Drip
does not ship it to consumer projects: the release `dist/` carries no icon
geometry, and consumers regenerate `ui/icon` with lucide_lustre. It therefore
appears only in this repository and in the built documentation site.

Most of that geometry is from Lucide, which is ISC-licensed; the icons Lucide
carries over from the Feather project (e.g. check, chevron-down, search, x) are
MIT-licensed. Both notices are reproduced below. The three brand marks are not
from Lucide and are covered under "Brand marks" further down.

